WEBVTT

1
00:01:43.401 --> 00:01:44.660
Three of a kind. Let's do this.

2
00:01:45.211 --> 00:01:46.338
That's it? Three guys?

3
00:01:46.339 --> 00:01:48.969
Two guys on the roof.
Every guy gets a share.

4
00:01:48.970 --> 00:01:49.970
Five shares is plenty.

5
00:01:49.971 --> 00:01:52.559
Six shares. Don't forget the
guy who planned the job.

6
00:01:52.560 --> 00:01:54.904
He thinks he can sit it out
and still take a slice?

7
00:01:54.905 --> 00:01:56.835
I know why they call him the Joker.

8
00:01:56.836 --> 00:01:58.146
So why do they call him the Joker?

9
00:01:58.425 --> 00:01:59.564
I heard he wears makeup.

10
00:01:59.565 --> 00:02:00.566
Makeup?

11
00:02:00.567 --> 00:02:02.304
Yeah! to scare people.
You know. warpaint?

12
00:02:14.761 --> 00:02:17.042
Alright everybody. hands up
heads down!

13
00:02:18.547 --> 00:02:21.029
I said. hands up.
heads down!

14
00:02:21.030 --> 00:02:24.207
Let's go pal! I'm
making a withdrawal here.

15
00:02:24.208 --> 00:02:26.169
Put your hands up!

16
00:02:26.604 --> 00:02:28.052
Here comes the silent alarm.

17
00:02:28.875 --> 00:02:30.045
There it goes.

18
00:02:30.046 --> 00:02:31.048
Heads down!

19
00:02:34.237 --> 00:02:35.941
Get down. I said stay
down there!

20
00:02:36.912 --> 00:02:40.314
That's funny it didn't dial out to 911.
I was trying to reach a private number.

21
00:02:40.315 --> 00:02:41.173
Is it a problem?

22
00:02:41.174 --> 00:02:42.175
No. I'm done here ...

23
00:03:00.933 --> 00:03:06.044
Obviously we don't want you doing anything 
with your hands other than holding on for dear life.

24
00:03:14.359 --> 00:03:16.332
On the ground! Stay on the ground!

25
00:03:16.333 --> 00:03:18.909
Nobody make a move! Nobody!

26
00:03:18.910 --> 00:03:20.281
Stay down!

27
00:03:36.397 --> 00:03:37.108
Come here!

28
00:03:40.050 --> 00:03:42.371
Do you have any idea who
you're stealing from?

29
00:03:42.530 --> 00:03:44.048
You and your friends are dead!

30
00:03:44.049 --> 00:03:45.766
He's out. right?

31
00:03:58.479 --> 00:04:00.065
Where did you learn to count?

32
00:04:02.956 --> 00:04:05.192
They wired this thing up with like 5000 Volts.

33
00:04:05.193 --> 00:04:06.195
What kind of bank does that?

34
00:04:06.196 --> 00:04:07.197
A mob bank.

35
00:04:07.198 --> 00:04:09.610
I guess the Joker is
as crazy as they say.

36
00:04:09.611 --> 00:04:10.611
Where is the alarm guy?

37
00:04:10.612 --> 00:04:13.184
The boss told me when the guy
was done. I should take him out.

38
00:04:13.422 --> 00:04:15.103
One less share. right?

39
00:04:15.917 --> 00:04:18.250
Funny ... He told me something similar.

40
00:04:18.251 --> 00:04:19.834
He what? No. no!

41
00:04:32.100 --> 00:04:36.971
That's a lot of money. If this Joker guy was so
smart he'd had us bring a bigger car.

42
00:04:38.580 --> 00:04:42.215
I'm betting the Joker told you to kill
me as soon as we loaded the cash.

43
00:04:43.463 --> 00:04:46.580
No. no. no. no ...
I kill the bus driver.

44
00:04:47.784 --> 00:04:48.921
Bus driver?

45
00:04:50.858 --> 00:04:52.295
What bus driver?

46
00:04:56.712 --> 00:04:58.472
School's out. Time to go.

47
00:04:58.876 --> 00:05:00.480
Cat's not getting up. is he?

48
00:05:01.873 --> 00:05:02.980
That's a lot of money.

49
00:05:06.800 --> 00:05:08.391
What happened to the rest of the guys?

50
00:05:16.247 --> 00:05:17.473
You think you're smart. huh?

51
00:05:18.949 --> 00:05:20.732
Well. the guy that hired you

52
00:05:21.115 --> 00:05:23.006
will just do the same with you.

53
00:05:24.256 --> 00:05:27.132
Ah. criminals in this town used
to believe in things.

54
00:05:27.133 --> 00:05:32.610
Honor. respect! Look at you!
What do you believe in?

55
00:05:32.611 --> 00:05:34.466
Huh. what do you believe in?

56
00:05:34.467 --> 00:05:39.036
I believe whatever doesn't kill
you simply makes you...

57
00:05:41.171 --> 00:05:43.009
stranger.

58
00:06:25.444 --> 00:06:28.609
Mr. Mayor. you were elected in
the campaign to clean up the city.

59
00:06:28.610 --> 00:06:29.611
When are you going to start?

60
00:06:29.612 --> 00:06:30.932
Well. Mike. I believe I already have.

61
00:06:30.933 --> 00:06:33.233
Like the so-called Batman? We're
hearing that he's doing some good.

62
00:06:33.234 --> 00:06:34.949
That criminals are running scared.
But I say ...

63
00:06:34.950 --> 00:06:36.894
Nah. man... I don't like it tonight.

64
00:06:37.437 --> 00:06:38.729
What are you? Superstitious?

65
00:06:38.730 --> 00:06:41.316
You got more chance of winning
the powerball than running into him.

66
00:06:41.317 --> 00:06:43.577
That simply is not true.
I'm told that

67
00:06:43.578 --> 00:06:45.082
Our men in the major crimes unit
are close to ...

68
00:06:45.083 --> 00:06:47.962
Mayor says you're closing
in on the Batman.

69
00:06:48.528 --> 00:06:51.001
The investigation is ongoing.

70
00:06:59.918 --> 00:07:02.060
Ever intending to see your wife
again. lieutenant?

71
00:07:02.061 --> 00:07:04.381
I thought you had to go
look after your mother. detective?

72
00:07:05.045 --> 00:07:06.369
Checked her back into the hospital.

73
00:07:07.416 --> 00:07:08.287
Sorry.

74
00:07:09.705 --> 00:07:10.766
So he hasn't shown up?

75
00:07:11.112 --> 00:07:12.264
I hope he doesn't.

76
00:07:13.117 --> 00:07:15.212
I like reminding everybody
that he's out there.

77
00:07:15.544 --> 00:07:16.664
Why wouldn't he come?

78
00:07:16.665 --> 00:07:20.087
Hopefully because he is busy.

79
00:07:37.286 --> 00:07:39.746
That's why we bring dogs.

80
00:07:40.430 --> 00:07:42.427
Hey. my filhotinhos.

81
00:07:46.529 --> 00:07:48.526
Look what your drugs
did to my customers.

82
00:07:49.572 --> 00:07:54.071
Buyer beware. I told you
my compound would take you places.

83
00:07:54.600 --> 00:07:57.344
I never said they'd be places
you wanted to go.

84
00:07:57.506 --> 00:07:59.802
My business repeat customers.

85
00:08:00.176 --> 00:08:03.112
If you don't like what I have to offer
you can buy from someone else.

86
00:08:04.056 --> 00:08:06.693
Assuming Batman left
anyone to buy from...

87
00:08:10.497 --> 00:08:13.112
My dogs are hungry!

88
00:08:17.772 --> 00:08:20.237
Pity there is only one of you.

89
00:08:28.985 --> 00:08:29.961
That's not him.

90
00:08:48.294 --> 00:08:49.522
That's more like it.

91
00:10:18.665 --> 00:10:20.147
Don't let me find you out here again.

92
00:10:20.693 --> 00:10:21.826
We are trying to help you.

93
00:10:22.184 --> 00:10:23.115
I don't need help!

94
00:10:23.390 --> 00:10:24.610
Not my diagnosis.

95
00:10:25.082 --> 00:10:26.025
What gives you the right?

96
00:10:26.704 --> 00:10:28.182
What's the difference between you and me?

97
00:10:28.711 --> 00:10:30.663
I'm not wearing hockey pads.

98
00:10:39.288 --> 00:10:41.450
He can't resist showing us
his face.

99
00:10:46.748 --> 00:10:48.253
What's he hiding
under that makeup?

100
00:10:56.691 --> 00:10:58.641
Can we get a minute.
people. please?

101
00:11:01.568 --> 00:11:03.963
Him again?
Who were the others?

102
00:11:03.964 --> 00:11:05.555
Another bunch of smalltimers.

103
00:11:06.701 --> 00:11:08.398
Some of the marked
bills I gave you.

104
00:11:08.399 --> 00:11:10.811
My detectives have been making
drug buys with them for weeks.

105
00:11:10.812 --> 00:11:13.765
This bank puts another draft of the mob.
That makes five.

106
00:11:13.766 --> 00:11:15.375
We found a bulk of the dirty cash.

107
00:11:15.376 --> 00:11:16.543
Time to move in.

108
00:11:16.544 --> 00:11:20.832
We would have to hit all banks
simultaneously. Swat teams. backup.

109
00:11:20.833 --> 00:11:22.604
What about this Joker guy?

110
00:11:22.605 --> 00:11:25.638
One man or the entire mob?
He can wait.

111
00:11:25.639 --> 00:11:28.028
When the new DA hears
about this. he'll want in.

112
00:11:28.107 --> 00:11:29.349
Do you trust him?

113
00:11:29.350 --> 00:11:33.716
It'd be hard to keep him out.
I hear he is as stubborn as you are.

114
00:12:18.135 --> 00:12:20.259
It would be nice when Wayne
manor is rebuilt.

115
00:12:21.568 --> 00:12:25.626
You can swap not sleeping in a penthouse
to not sleeping in a mansion.

116
00:12:25.821 --> 00:12:29.860
Whenever you stich yourself up
you do make a bloody mess.

117
00:12:29.861 --> 00:12:32.595
Yeah. It makes me
learn from my mistakes.

118
00:12:32.792 --> 00:12:35.429
You ought to be pretty
knowledgable by now.

119
00:12:37.943 --> 00:12:42.691
My armor. Carrying too
much weight. I need to be faster.

120
00:12:42.990 --> 00:12:44.681
I'm sure Mr. Fox
can oblige.

121
00:12:45.822 --> 00:12:47.417
Did you get mauled by a tiger?

122
00:12:47.418 --> 00:12:48.419
It was a dog.

123
00:12:48.420 --> 00:12:50.314
- Ah?
- It was a big dog.

124
00:12:51.836 --> 00:12:54.925
More copycats last night.
Alfred. With guns.

125
00:12:54.926 --> 00:12:57.162
Why don't you hire them
and take a weekend off?

126
00:12:57.163 --> 00:13:02.634
That wasn't ... exactly what I had in mind
when I said I wanted to inspire people.

127
00:13:02.635 --> 00:13:03.636
I know.

128
00:13:04.243 --> 00:13:07.627
But things have improved.
Look at the new district attorney.

129
00:13:08.784 --> 00:13:10.720
I am. Closely.

130
00:13:11.109 --> 00:13:12.764
I need to know if he can be trusted.

131
00:13:13.264 --> 00:13:16.604
Are you interested in his character
or ... his sexual circle?

132
00:13:21.568 --> 00:13:24.187
Who Rachel spends her time
with is her business.

133
00:13:26.076 --> 00:13:28.305
I trust you don't have
me followed on my day off.

134
00:13:28.306 --> 00:13:29.650
If you ever took
one I might.

135
00:13:32.196 --> 00:13:34.101
Know your limits. Master Wayne.

136
00:13:34.102 --> 00:13:37.077
Batman has no limits.

137
00:13:37.504 --> 00:13:38.754
Well you do. sir.

138
00:13:38.755 --> 00:13:40.536
Well. I can't afford to know them.

139
00:13:40.537 --> 00:13:42.884
What's going to happen on
the day that you find out?

140
00:13:42.885 --> 00:13:45.747
We'll all know how much you
like to say: "I told you so"

141
00:13:45.748 --> 00:13:50.965
On that day. Master Wayne. even
I won't want to. Probably.

142
00:13:58.053 --> 00:13:59.324
Sorry I'm late. folks.

143
00:14:03.499 --> 00:14:04.477
Where were you?

144
00:14:04.478 --> 00:14:05.771
Worried you'd have to step up?

145
00:14:05.772 --> 00:14:08.301
Harvey. I know these
briefs backwards.

146
00:14:08.302 --> 00:14:13.238
Fair's fair.
Heads. I'll take it. Tails. he's all yours.

147
00:14:13.239 --> 00:14:15.672
Oh yeah? You want to flip a coin
to see who leads?

148
00:14:15.673 --> 00:14:16.784
It's my father's lucky coin.

149
00:14:17.175 --> 00:14:19.188
As I recall. it got me my
first date with you.

150
00:14:19.189 --> 00:14:21.285
You wouldn't leave something
like that up to chance.

151
00:14:22.633 --> 00:14:25.551
I don't.
I make my own luck.

152
00:14:27.119 --> 00:14:30.557
All rise!
The Honorable Judge Surrillo presiding.

153
00:14:31.514 --> 00:14:33.916
I thought the DA just plays
golf with the mayor or things like that.

154
00:14:34.066 --> 00:14:37.920
Tee-off is 1:30. More than enough time
to put you away for life. Salli.

155
00:14:38.021 --> 00:14:41.848
With Carmine Falcone in Arkham. someone must have
stepped up to run this so-called family.

156
00:14:43.675 --> 00:14:49.441
Is that man in this courtroom today?
Could you identify him for us please?

157
00:14:49.672 --> 00:14:51.665
You win. counsellor.

158
00:14:53.325 --> 00:14:54.686
It was me!

159
00:14:56.588 --> 00:15:00.476
I have a sworn statement
from you. that this man.

160
00:15:00.477 --> 00:15:04.245
Salvatore Maroni. is the new
head of the Falcone crime family.

161
00:15:04.545 --> 00:15:08.539
Maroni? He is a fallguy!
I'm the brains of the organization.

162
00:15:09.850 --> 00:15:10.602
Order. order!

163
00:15:11.052 --> 00:15:12.183
Permission to treat
the witness as hostile.

164
00:15:12.253 --> 00:15:12.603
Granted.

165
00:15:12.703 --> 00:15:14.526
Hostile?
I'll show you hostile!

166
00:15:20.110 --> 00:15:22.916
Carbon fiber.
.28 caliber. made in China.

167
00:15:22.917 --> 00:15:26.157
If you want to kill a public servant. Mr. Maroni.
I recommend you buy American.

168
00:15:27.818 --> 00:15:29.019
Get him out of here!

169
00:15:29.469 --> 00:15:30.620
But. your honor. I'm not done!

170
00:15:34.113 --> 00:15:36.026
We will never be able to link
the gun to Maroni.

171
00:15:36.027 --> 00:15:38.053
so we won't be able to
charge him. but the fact

172
00:15:38.078 --> 00:15:40.615
they are trying to kill you.
means we are getting to them.

173
00:15:40.616 --> 00:15:43.972
Well I'm glad you're so pleased Rachel.
And I'm fine. by the way.

174
00:15:43.973 --> 00:15:46.555
Come on Harvey. you are Gotham's DA!
If you are not getting shot at....

175
00:15:46.565 --> 00:15:48.087
you're not doing your job right.

176
00:15:48.950 --> 00:15:53.191
But you know. he said if you were rattled
you could take the rest of the day off.

177
00:15:53.192 --> 00:15:56.845
I can't. I dragged the Head of
the major crimes unit down here.

178
00:15:56.920 --> 00:16:00.848
Jim Gordon? He's a friend actually.
try to be nice!

179
00:16:10.457 --> 00:16:12.860
I hear you got a
hell of a right cross.

180
00:16:16.562 --> 00:16:18.881
It's a shame Sal's gonna walk.

181
00:16:18.882 --> 00:16:20.328
Yeah. well good thing about the mob is...

182
00:16:20.329 --> 00:16:22.048
They keep giving you second chances.

183
00:16:28.025 --> 00:16:32.629
Lightly radiated bills.
Fancy stuff for a city cop.

184
00:16:32.849 --> 00:16:33.479
Have helped?

185
00:16:33.611 --> 00:16:35.604
We have links with various agents ...

186
00:16:35.605 --> 00:16:37.394
Save it Gordon. I want to meet him.

187
00:16:37.395 --> 00:16:41.052
Official policy is to arrest the
vigilante known as Batman on sight.

188
00:16:41.119 --> 00:16:43.649
Uhum ... And what about that floodlight
on the top of MCU?

189
00:16:43.669 --> 00:16:46.459
If you've got problems
with malfunctioning equipment.

190
00:16:46.460 --> 00:16:48.781
I suggest you take them up
with maintenance counselor.

191
00:16:49.395 --> 00:16:52.284
I put every known money launderer
in Gotham. behind bars.

192
00:16:52.285 --> 00:16:53.906
but the Mob is still getting its money.

193
00:16:55.211 --> 00:16:58.804
I think you and your friend.
have found the last game in town

194
00:16:58.805 --> 00:17:02.246
and are trying to hit them where it hurts:
their wallets. That's bold.

195
00:17:03.934 --> 00:17:05.060
You gonna count me in?

196
00:17:05.461 --> 00:17:08.621
In this town the fewer people know
something. the safer the operation.

197
00:17:08.722 --> 00:17:11.211
Gordon. I don't like that you've got your
own special unit and

198
00:17:11.306 --> 00:17:14.178
I don't like that is full of cops
I investigated at internal affairs.

199
00:17:14.179 --> 00:17:18.802
If I had to work with cops you investigated while you
were licking your name at IAIP working alone.

200
00:17:19.523 --> 00:17:21.470
I don't get political points
for being an idealist.

201
00:17:21.471 --> 00:17:23.325
I have to do the best I can
with what I have.

202
00:17:27.043 --> 00:17:29.530
You want me to back warrants
for search and seizure

203
00:17:29.531 --> 00:17:32.858
on five banks without telling
me what we're after?

204
00:17:33.787 --> 00:17:36.789
Well. I can give you
the names of the banks.

205
00:17:37.306 --> 00:17:38.494
Well. that's a start.

206
00:17:39.302 --> 00:17:41.594
I'll get you your warrants.
but I want your trust.

207
00:17:41.995 --> 00:17:46.069
You don't have to sell me. Dent. We all
know you're Gotham's white knight.

208
00:17:47.550 --> 00:17:50.202
I heard they have a different name
for me down at MCU.

209
00:17:50.922 --> 00:17:52.354
I wouldn't know about that.

210
00:17:53.457 --> 00:17:57.199
In China. Lau Security Investments
stands for dynamic new growth.

211
00:17:57.409 --> 00:18:01.365
The joint Chinese venture with
Wayne Enterprises will be a powerhouse.

212
00:18:01.763 --> 00:18:06.229
Well. Mr Lau. I speak
for the rest of the board ...

213
00:18:07.652 --> 00:18:10.219
And Mr. Wayne.
in expressing our own excitement.

214
00:18:15.296 --> 00:18:19.530
Sir. I know that Mr. Wayne is curious
about how his trust fund gets replenished

215
00:18:19.582 --> 00:18:21.522
But frankly ...
This is embarrasing!

216
00:18:21.783 --> 00:18:23.846
You worry about the delegace.
Mr. Reese.

217
00:18:24.492 --> 00:18:26.053
I'll worry about Bruce Wayne.

218
00:18:27.137 --> 00:18:30.271
It's done.
The numbers are solid.

219
00:18:30.571 --> 00:18:34.942
Do them again. Wouldn't want the
trust fund to run out. now would we?

220
00:18:38.178 --> 00:18:43.403
Another long night? This joint venture
was your idea and the consultants love it.

221
00:18:43.703 --> 00:18:47.956
But I am not convinced. Lau's company
has grown by 8% anually like clockwork.

222
00:18:48.588 --> 00:18:52.401
His revenue stream must be
off the books. It may be even illegal.

223
00:18:53.082 --> 00:18:54.673
OK. cancel the deal.

224
00:18:55.906 --> 00:18:57.356
You already knew?

225
00:18:57.586 --> 00:19:00.079
I just needed a closer look at their books.

226
00:19:00.682 --> 00:19:02.352
Anything else you can trouble me for?

227
00:19:02.948 --> 00:19:03.823
I need a new suit.

228
00:19:04.651 --> 00:19:07.225
Yeah ... 3 buttons is a little
90's. Mr. Wayne.

229
00:19:07.506 --> 00:19:10.718
I am not talking fashion
Mr Fox. so much as function.

230
00:19:11.445 --> 00:19:15.398
- Want to be able to turn your head?
- Sure would make backing out of the driveway easier.

231
00:19:15.765 --> 00:19:17.195
I'll see what I can do.

232
00:19:22.420 --> 00:19:24.467
It took me 3 weeks to
get a reservation here.

233
00:19:24.468 --> 00:19:26.566
And I had to tell them
I work for the government.

234
00:19:26.601 --> 00:19:27.316
Really?

235
00:19:27.317 --> 00:19:29.389
This city health inspector is
not afraid to pull strings.

236
00:19:29.774 --> 00:19:31.786
Rachel!
Fancy that!

237
00:19:32.118 --> 00:19:34.857
Yeah Bruce. fancy that.

238
00:19:35.085 --> 00:19:37.093
Rachel. Natasha.
Natasha. Rachel.

239
00:19:36.843 --> 00:19:42.148
- Natasha. are you the. ..
- The prima ballerina from the Moscow ballet.

240
00:19:42.519 --> 00:19:44.060
Wow. Harvey's
taking me next week.

241
00:19:44.564 --> 00:19:46.262
Really?
So you're into ballet?

242
00:19:46.656 --> 00:19:48.933
Bruce. this is Harvey Dent.

243
00:19:49.235 --> 00:19:52.818
The famous Bruce Wayne.
Rachel's told me everything about you.

244
00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:54.206
Well. I certainly hope not.

245
00:19:54.830 --> 00:19:56.344
So. let's put a couple of tables together.

246
00:19:56.846 --> 00:20:00.390
- I'm not sure that they'll let us.
- Oh they should. I own the place.

247
00:20:01.526 --> 00:20:04.083
How could want to raise children
in a city like this?

248
00:20:04.084 --> 00:20:06.615
Well. I was raised here.
I turned out OK.

249
00:20:06.967 --> 00:20:08.443
Is Wayne manor in the city limits?

250
00:20:09.471 --> 00:20:11.876
The Palisades.

251
00:20:11.945 --> 00:20:13.033
You know as our new DA.

252
00:20:13.034 --> 00:20:15.914
you might want to figure out
where your jurisdiction ends.

253
00:20:16.743 --> 00:20:20.699
I'm talking about the kind of city
that idolizes a masked vigilante.

254
00:20:20.785 --> 00:20:24.136
Gotham City is proud of an ordinary
citizen standing up for what's right.

255
00:20:24.238 --> 00:20:26.778
Gotham needs heroes
like you. elected officials.

256
00:20:26.779 --> 00:20:28.441
And not a man who
thinks he's above the law.

257
00:20:28.534 --> 00:20:30.606
- Exactly. Who appointed the Batman?
- We did.

258
00:20:30.865 --> 00:20:34.268
All of us who stood by
and let scum take control of our city.

259
00:20:34.278 --> 00:20:35.969
But this is a democracy. Harvey.

260
00:20:36.099 --> 00:20:37.658
When their enemies were at the gates.

261
00:20:37.659 --> 00:20:41.166
the Romans would suspend democracy
and appoint one man to protect the city.

262
00:20:41.742 --> 00:20:44.517
It wasn't considered an honor.
It was considered a public service.

263
00:20:44.583 --> 00:20:48.794
Harvey. the last man that they appointed
to protect the republic was named Caesar.

264
00:20:48.795 --> 00:20:50.146
and he never gave up his power.

265
00:20:50.714 --> 00:20:53.886
OK. fine.
You either die a hero...

266
00:20:53.986 --> 00:20:56.676
or you live long enough to see
yourself become the villain.

267
00:20:57.079 --> 00:21:01.533
Look. Whoever the Batman is. he doesn't
want to do this for the rest of his life.

268
00:21:01.604 --> 00:21:04.300
Batman is looking for someone
to take up his mantle.

269
00:21:04.417 --> 00:21:09.761
- Someone like you. Mr. Dent?
- Maybe. If I'm up to it.

270
00:21:09.762 --> 00:21:14.273
- What if Harvey Dent is
the caped crusader?

271
00:21:16.938 --> 00:21:20.191
- If I were sneaking out every night.
someone would have noticed by now.

272
00:21:22.694 --> 00:21:26.878
Well ... I'm sold that I'm going
to throw you a fundraiser.

273
00:21:27.035 --> 00:21:30.101
That's nice of you Bruce. but
I'm not up for reelection for 3 years.

274
00:21:30.251 --> 00:21:33.833
No. you don't understand.
One fundraiser with my pals.

275
00:21:35.335 --> 00:21:37.102
you'll never need another cent.

276
00:21:52.122 --> 00:21:53.733
What the hell is this?

277
00:21:55.900 --> 00:21:58.991
As you all are aware. one of
our deposits was stolen.

278
00:21:59.211 --> 00:22:02.455
A relatively small amount.
68 million.

279
00:22:02.882 --> 00:22:05.456
Who is stupid enough to steal from us?

280
00:22:05.457 --> 00:22:08.980
2-bit wackjob. wears a cheap
purple suit and makeup.

281
00:22:09.498 --> 00:22:11.051
He's not the problem.
He's a nobody.

282
00:22:11.445 --> 00:22:14.743
The problem is our money
being tracked by the cops.

283
00:22:14.964 --> 00:22:17.115
Thanks to Mr. Maroni's
well placed sources.

284
00:22:17.116 --> 00:22:19.867
we know that police have
indeed identified our banks

285
00:22:20.048 --> 00:22:24.162
using marked bills and are planning
to seize your funds today.

286
00:22:24.263 --> 00:22:28.561
And since the enthusiastic new DA has
put all my competitors out of business.

287
00:22:28.562 --> 00:22:30.689
I'm your only option.

288
00:22:30.740 --> 00:22:31.897
So what do you propose?

289
00:22:32.532 --> 00:22:34.856
Moving all deposits
to one secure location.

290
00:22:35.254 --> 00:22:37.053
- Not a bank.
- Where then?

291
00:22:37.054 --> 00:22:38.916
Nobody can know. but me.

292
00:22:38.917 --> 00:22:43.939
If the police were to gain leverage over one
of you. everyone's money would be at stake.

293
00:22:44.142 --> 00:22:46.147
What stop them getting to you?

294
00:22:46.149 --> 00:22:49.155
I go to Hong Kong.
Far from Dent's jurisdiction

295
00:22:49.834 --> 00:22:52.109
And the Chinese will not extradite
one of their own.

296
00:22:53.060 --> 00:22:54.565
How soon can we move the money?

297
00:22:54.841 --> 00:22:56.403
I already have.

298
00:22:58.385 --> 00:23:00.907
For obvious reasons. I couldn't
wait for your permission.

299
00:23:01.497 --> 00:23:04.591
Rest assured your money is safe.

300
00:23:17.753 --> 00:23:19.984
And I thought my
jokes were bad.

301
00:23:20.014 --> 00:23:22.908
Give me one reason why I shouldn't
have my boy here pull your head off.

302
00:23:22.998 --> 00:23:24.469
How about a magic trick?

303
00:23:27.760 --> 00:23:30.448
I'm going to make
this pencil disappear.

304
00:23:32.317 --> 00:23:36.976
Tahdah! It's gone!

305
00:23:38.072 --> 00:23:40.303
Oh. and by the way.
the suit. it wasn't cheap.

306
00:23:40.304 --> 00:23:42.093
You ought to know.
you bought it!

307
00:23:42.475 --> 00:23:46.872
Easy.
I want to hear the opposition.

308
00:23:50.084 --> 00:23:52.580
Let's wind the clock back a year.

309
00:23:52.581 --> 00:23:57.907
These cops and lawyers wouldn't dare
cross any of you.

310
00:24:01.164 --> 00:24:04.482
What happened?
Did your balls drop off?

311
00:24:06.396 --> 00:24:09.627
- You see a guy like me ...
- A freak!

312
00:24:12.064 --> 00:24:19.571
A guy like me ..
I know why you choose to have

313
00:24:20.173 --> 00:24:26.093
group therapy sessions in broad daylight.
I know why you're afraid to go out at night.

314
00:24:28.108 --> 00:24:35.019
The Batman. Batman has shown Gotham
your true colors. unfortunately.

315
00:24:35.376 --> 00:24:38.164
Dent. he's just the beginning.

316
00:24:39.481 --> 00:24:44.214
And as for the television's
so-called plan ...

317
00:24:44.215 --> 00:24:49.142
The Batman has no jurisdiction.
He'll find him and make him squeal.

318
00:24:49.240 --> 00:24:52.252
I know the squealers when I see them.

319
00:24:55.045 --> 00:24:59.538
- What do you propose?
- It's simple. We kill the Batman.

320
00:25:00.439 --> 00:25:03.363
If it is so simple why
haven't you done it already?

321
00:25:03.564 --> 00:25:06.116
If you are good thing at something.
never do it for free.

322
00:25:06.609 --> 00:25:08.068
And what you want?

323
00:25:09.054 --> 00:25:11.106
Hm ... Half.

324
00:25:12.553 --> 00:25:17.650
- Are you crazy!
- No I'm not ... No. I'm not.

325
00:25:19.578 --> 00:25:27.398
If we don't deal with this now.
soon little Gamble here

326
00:25:27.399 --> 00:25:30.342
won't be able to get a
nickel for his grandma.

327
00:25:30.589 --> 00:25:32.809
Enough from the clown!

328
00:25:32.810 --> 00:25:37.811
Let's not blow this out of proportion.

329
00:25:37.812 --> 00:25:40.799
Do you think you can
steal from us and just walk away?

330
00:25:40.834 --> 00:25:44.952
I'm putting a word out: 500 grand
for this clown dead.

331
00:25:44.953 --> 00:25:48.301
A million alive. so I can
teach him some manners first.

332
00:25:49.006 --> 00:25:52.704
Alright. so listen.
Why don't you give me a call when

333
00:25:52.705 --> 00:25:58.499
you wanna start taking things
a little more seriously? Here's my card.

334
00:26:18.184 --> 00:26:21.521
You're a hard man to reach.

335
00:26:23.200 --> 00:26:25.291
Lau is halfway to Hong Kong.

336
00:26:27.213 --> 00:26:28.799
If he had asked.
I could have taken his passport.

337
00:26:28.800 --> 00:26:30.297
I told you to keep me in the loop.

338
00:26:30.332 --> 00:26:34.040
All that was left in the vaults were
marked bills. They knew we were coming.

339
00:26:34.041 --> 00:26:36.022
As soon as your office got involved ...

340
00:26:36.057 --> 00:26:37.100
My office?

341
00:26:37.101 --> 00:26:40.398
You're sitting down there with scum like
Wuertz and Ramirez and you're talking ...

342
00:26:41.276 --> 00:26:44.629
Oh yeah Gordon. I almost had your rookie
cold on a racketeering beef.

343
00:26:44.634 --> 00:26:48.157
Don't try and cloud the fact that clearly
Maroni's got people in your office. Dent.

344
00:26:52.216 --> 00:26:53.177
We need Lau back.

345
00:26:54.304 --> 00:26:57.159
But the Chinese won't extradite
a National under any circumstances.

346
00:26:58.472 --> 00:27:01.395
If I get him to you.
can you get him to talk?

347
00:27:01.411 --> 00:27:03.196
I'll get him to sing.

348
00:27:02.441 --> 00:27:04.577
We're going after the mob's life savings.

349
00:27:05.550 --> 00:27:06.920
Things will get ugly ...

350
00:27:07.292 --> 00:27:09.483
I knew the risk
when I took this job. lieutenant.

351
00:27:09.683 --> 00:27:10.924
How will you get him back ...

352
00:27:13.736 --> 00:27:15.094
He does that.

353
00:27:15.489 --> 00:27:18.841
Our Chinese friends left town before I
could tell them the deal was off.

354
00:27:18.961 --> 00:27:21.854
Well I'm sure you've always
wanted to go to Hong Kong.

355
00:27:23.065 --> 00:27:24.011
What's wrong with a phone call?

356
00:27:25.262 --> 00:27:28.400
I think Mr Lau
deserves a more ... personal touch.

357
00:27:30.102 --> 00:27:34.572
Now for high altitude jumps. you're
gonna need oxygen and stabilizers.

358
00:27:41.753 --> 00:27:43.699
But what about getting back into the plane?

359
00:27:44.182 --> 00:27:45.967
I'd recommend a good travel agent.

360
00:27:45.867 --> 00:27:47.278
Without it landing.

361
00:27:48.983 --> 00:27:51.404
Now that's more like it. Mr. Wayne.

362
00:27:52.341 --> 00:27:58.042
The ClA had a program back in the 60's for getting
their people out of hot spots called skyhook

363
00:27:58.627 --> 00:28:02.963
You could look into that.
Okay. now.

364
00:28:04.306 --> 00:28:07.307
Hardened Kevlar plates over
titanium-tipped

365
00:28:07.308 --> 00:28:09.793
triweaved fibers for flexibility.

366
00:28:10.040 --> 00:28:13.133
You'll be lighter.
faster. more agile.

367
00:28:16.296 --> 00:28:18.847
Perhaps you should read the instructions first.

368
00:28:19.339 --> 00:28:20.427
Now there is a tradeoff.

369
00:28:20.428 --> 00:28:24.316
Separation of the plates makes you
more vulnerable to knives and gunfire.

370
00:28:24.351 --> 00:28:26.656
We wouldn't want to make
things too easy now. would we?

371
00:28:27.381 --> 00:28:29.523
How will it hold up against dogs?

372
00:28:29.808 --> 00:28:32.210
We talking Rotweilers or Chiuauas?

373
00:28:33.182 --> 00:28:35.027
It should do fine against cats.

374
00:28:35.564 --> 00:28:37.620
I found one in Arizona.

375
00:28:38.044 --> 00:28:42.151
An very nice man said he could have it up
and running in a week and he'd take the cash.

376
00:28:42.521 --> 00:28:43.538
What about a flight crew?

377
00:28:43.539 --> 00:28:48.001
South Korean smugglers; they run flights
into Pyongyang below radar the whole way.

378
00:28:48.002 --> 00:28:49.002
Did you think of an alibi?

379
00:28:49.177 --> 00:28:50.368
Oh. yes.

380
00:28:59.690 --> 00:29:03.380
Presentation cancelled

381
00:29:09.416 --> 00:29:11.748
I believe this is your plane. sir!

382
00:29:15.802 --> 00:29:19.015
You look tired. Alfred.
Will you be all right without me?

383
00:29:21.229 --> 00:29:24.473
If you can tell me the Russian for:
Apply your own bloody suntan lotion.

384
00:29:35.673 --> 00:29:39.935
Yo Gamble. somebody here for you.
They say they've just killed the Joker.

385
00:29:40.175 --> 00:29:41.977
And they brought the body.

386
00:29:59.143 --> 00:30:00.495
Dead. that's 500 ...

387
00:30:02.311 --> 00:30:04.208
How about alive?

388
00:30:07.695 --> 00:30:10.128
You want to know how I
got these scars?

389
00:30:12.316 --> 00:30:18.441
My father was a drinker and a fiend.

390
00:30:19.513 --> 00:30:23.516
One night he goes off
crazier than usual

391
00:30:23.926 --> 00:30:26.566
Mommy gets the kitchen knife
to defend herself.

392
00:30:26.967 --> 00:30:31.482
He does not like that.
Not one bit.

393
00:30:32.487 --> 00:30:39.232
So. me watching. he takes the
knife to her. laughing while he does it.

394
00:30:39.882 --> 00:30:45.685
He turns to me and he says:
Why so serious. son?

395
00:30:46.988 --> 00:30:49.431
He comes at me with the knife ...

396
00:30:49.497 --> 00:30:55.914
Why so serious. son? He sticks
the blade in my mouth:

397
00:30:56.658 --> 00:31:00.158
Let's put a smile on that face!

398
00:31:06.447 --> 00:31:07.791
Why so serious?

399
00:31:12.788 --> 00:31:22.662
Now. our operation is small but there is a
lot of potential for aggressive expansion.

400
00:31:22.663 --> 00:31:26.445
So. which of you fine gentleman
would like to join our team?

401
00:31:27.265 --> 00:31:29.064
There's only one spot open right now.

402
00:31:29.099 --> 00:31:33.227
So we're going to
have tryouts?

403
00:31:37.906 --> 00:31:39.492
Make it fast.

404
00:31:49.704 --> 00:31:51.107
Welcome to Hong Kong. Mr. Fox.

405
00:31:51.108 --> 00:31:53.792
Mr Lau regrets he isn't able
to greet you in person today.

406
00:31:54.116 --> 00:31:55.403
I understand.

407
00:32:05.554 --> 00:32:08.928
For security purposes. I'm going to
have to ask you to check in your mobile.

408
00:32:09.561 --> 00:32:10.986
Of course

409
00:32:13.591 --> 00:32:16.978
I must apologize for leaving
Gotham in the middle of our negotiations.

410
00:32:16.979 --> 00:32:20.868
This misunderstanding
with the Gotham police force.

411
00:32:21.240 --> 00:32:23.521
I couldn't let such a thing
threaten my company.

412
00:32:23.530 --> 00:32:24.277
Of course.

413
00:32:24.203 --> 00:32:26.526
A businessman of your stature
will understand

414
00:32:26.527 --> 00:32:30.531
that with you here now.
we can continue.

415
00:32:31.702 --> 00:32:35.442
Well I do appreciate you bringing me
out here in such style Mr Lau ...

416
00:32:36.874 --> 00:32:41.070
- We do not allow cell phones in here.
- Oh sorry. forgot I had it.

417
00:32:41.452 --> 00:32:46.521
I really came to tell you that
our business deal has to be put on hold.

418
00:32:46.702 --> 00:32:53.398
We can't afford to be seen to do business
with ... whatever it is you're accused of being.

419
00:32:53.404 --> 00:32:56.000
I'm sure a businessman of
your stature will understand.

420
00:32:56.215 --> 00:33:00.000
I think Mr Fox. a
simple phone call might have sufficed.

421
00:33:00.177 --> 00:33:01.510
Mr. Wayne didn't want
you to think that

422
00:33:01.511 --> 00:33:03.532
he was deliberately
wasting your time.

423
00:33:03.600 --> 00:33:05.477
Just accidentally wasting it.

424
00:33:06.472 --> 00:33:10.218
That's very good Mr Lau.
Accidentally. very good.

425
00:33:10.982 --> 00:33:11.876
Hey. sir!

426
00:33:30.293 --> 00:33:32.345
A better view from the train.

427
00:33:32.546 --> 00:33:38.515
- How's the view from LSl hallways?
- Restricted. Lau has held up the networking tight.

428
00:33:38.616 --> 00:33:40.795
- What is this?
- I had RND work it up.

429
00:33:40.796 --> 00:33:44.092
It sends out a high frequency pulse
records in response time.

430
00:33:44.093 --> 00:33:45.376
For mapping an environment.

431
00:33:45.530 --> 00:33:50.933
- Sonar. just like a ...
- a submarine. Mr. Wayne.

432
00:33:50.934 --> 00:33:53.268
- And the other device?
- It's in place.

433
00:33:54.123 --> 00:33:57.333
Mr Wayne. good luck.

434
00:35:36.553 --> 00:35:37.879
Where are the police?

435
00:35:38.173 --> 00:35:38.848
They are coming.

436
00:35:39.002 --> 00:35:40.800
Then what the hell
am I paying them for?

437
00:37:41.678 --> 00:37:43.203
Please deliver to Lieutenant Gordon.

438
00:37:47.436 --> 00:37:50.897
Look. give us the money
and we'll talk about making a deal.

439
00:37:51.240 --> 00:37:53.955
The money is the only reason
I am still alive.

440
00:37:54.580 --> 00:37:58.546
Oh. you mean when they find out
that you've helped us they're going to kill you?

441
00:37:58.547 --> 00:38:00.099
Are you threatening my client?

442
00:38:00.100 --> 00:38:03.876
No. I'm just assuming your
client's cooperation with this investigation.

443
00:38:06.647 --> 00:38:07.806
As well everyone.

444
00:38:09.249 --> 00:38:12.153
No?
Okay.

445
00:38:13.269 --> 00:38:15.655
Enjoy your time in county Mr Lau.

446
00:38:16.342 --> 00:38:19.614
Wait.
I won't give you the money.

447
00:38:20.269 --> 00:38:23.334
But I will give you my clients.
All of them.

448
00:38:23.335 --> 00:38:29.863
You were a glorified accountant. What could you
possibly have on all of them that we could charge?

449
00:38:29.864 --> 00:38:33.688
I'm good with calculation.
I handled all the investments.

450
00:38:33.908 --> 00:38:35.220
One big pot.

451
00:38:37.053 --> 00:38:39.872
- Got it.
- One minute.

452
00:38:41.496 --> 00:38:46.160
If they pull their money we can
charge them all as one crew on conspiracy.

453
00:38:46.161 --> 00:38:47.162
Charge them with what?

454
00:38:47.516 --> 00:38:50.908
In a Reiko case. if you can charge one
of the conspirators with a felony. you can ...

455
00:38:50.909 --> 00:38:52.734
Charge all of them with it. That's great.

456
00:38:54.536 --> 00:39:01.427
Mr Lau. What kind of details do you
have about this communal fund?

457
00:39:01.428 --> 00:39:02.429
Edgers. notebooks ...

458
00:39:02.172 --> 00:39:05.039
Immunity. protection and a
chartered plane back to Hong Kong.

459
00:39:05.040 --> 00:39:06.708
After you testify in open court.

460
00:39:06.879 --> 00:39:09.963
And I'm just curious.
with all your clients locked up.

461
00:39:09.998 --> 00:39:11.514
what's going to happen with all that money?

462
00:39:12.009 --> 00:39:15.297
Like I said. I am
good with calculation.

463
00:39:15.298 --> 00:39:20.084
He can't go to county.
I'll keep him here in the holding cells.

464
00:39:20.085 --> 00:39:21.871
What is this Gordon. your fortress?

465
00:39:22.782 --> 00:39:27.413
- Do you trust them over at county?
- I don't trust them here.

466
00:39:29.349 --> 00:39:30.730
Lau stays.

467
00:39:31.336 --> 00:39:35.505
Well. I don't know about Mr. Lau's travel
arrangements. but I'm sure glad he's back.

468
00:39:36.261 --> 00:39:38.710
He would. we should
have hired the clown.

469
00:39:41.302 --> 00:39:46.698
He was right. we have to
fix real problem. Batman.

470
00:39:51.354 --> 00:39:53.781
I'm not aware of any participation
by the Batman in the investigations.

471
00:39:53.782 --> 00:39:55.862
Our boy looks good on the tube

472
00:39:55.779 --> 00:39:58.661
You sure you want to embarrass me
in front of my friends lieutenant?

473
00:39:58.662 --> 00:40:01.588
No. don't worry.
They're coming too.

474
00:40:09.656 --> 00:40:11.387
Have a nice trip. See you in the next fall.

475
00:40:11.688 --> 00:40:15.846
712 counts of extortion.
849 counts of racketeering.

476
00:40:15.847 --> 00:40:21.107
246 counts of fraud.
87 counts of conspiracy. murder ...

477
00:40:22.393 --> 00:40:27.336
527 counts of obstruction of justice.
How do the defendants plead?

478
00:40:34.132 --> 00:40:35.546
Order in court.

479
00:40:35.547 --> 00:40:40.663
549 criminals at once. How did you
convince Surrillo to hear this farce?

480
00:40:40.664 --> 00:40:45.211
She shares my enthusiasm
for justice. After all she is a Judge.

481
00:40:45.212 --> 00:40:48.337
Even if you blow enough smoke
to get convinctions out of Surrillo.

482
00:40:48.338 --> 00:40:51.186
you're going to set a new record
in appeals for quickest tick in the ass.

483
00:40:51.221 --> 00:40:55.580
It won't matter. the head guys make bail.
sure. But the midlevel guys. they can't.

484
00:40:56.517 --> 00:40:59.006
They can't afford to be off
the streets long enough for trial and appeal.

485
00:40:59.007 --> 00:41:00.581
they'll cut deals that include some jailtime.

486
00:41:00.688 --> 00:41:03.607
Think of all you can do
with 18 months of clean streets.

487
00:41:05.278 --> 00:41:06.426
Mr. Mayor. you can't ...

488
00:41:06.427 --> 00:41:08.201
Get out. both of you.

489
00:41:12.632 --> 00:41:13.533
Sit down.

490
00:41:19.128 --> 00:41:22.200
The public likes you.
That's the only reason that this might fly.

491
00:41:22.201 --> 00:41:26.418
But that means it's on you. They are all going
to come after you now and not just the mob.

492
00:41:26.419 --> 00:41:33.022
Politicians. journalists. cops. Anyone
whose wallet is about to get lighter.

493
00:41:33.642 --> 00:41:38.134
Are you up to it? You better be.
because if they get anything on you

494
00:41:38.135 --> 00:41:43.168
and those criminals are back on the streets ...
Followed swiftly by you and me.

495
00:42:05.469 --> 00:42:07.989
I think your fundraiser will
be a great success sir.

496
00:42:07.990 --> 00:42:10.368
And why do you think I want to
hold a party for Harvey Dent?

497
00:42:10.369 --> 00:42:13.742
Well. I assumed it was your
usual reason for socializing

498
00:42:13.743 --> 00:42:16.079
beyond myself and the scum
of Gotham's underbelly.

499
00:42:16.080 --> 00:42:17.973
To try to impress Miss Dawes.

500
00:42:17.974 --> 00:42:23.147
Very droll. but very wrong.
Actually it's Dent.

501
00:42:23.148 --> 00:42:25.261
The police disclosed the footage
found at scene of the body.

502
00:42:25.262 --> 00:42:28.143
Sensitive viewers please be aware:
the image is disturbing.

503
00:42:28.344 --> 00:42:31.511
- Tell them your name.
- Brian.

504
00:42:33.680 --> 00:42:39.271
- Are you the real Batman?
- No! No!

505
00:42:39.272 --> 00:42:41.920
Then why do you dress up like him?

506
00:42:46.645 --> 00:42:51.770
- He's a symbol... that we don't have to be afraid of scum like you!
- Yeah. you do. Brian. You really do!

507
00:42:55.659 --> 00:43:00.223
So you think Batman has
made Gotham a better place?

508
00:43:08.232 --> 00:43:11.636
You see this is how crazy
Batman has made Gotham.

509
00:43:11.765 --> 00:43:18.385
If you want to order in Gotham the Batman
must take off his mask and turn himself in!

510
00:43:19.140 --> 00:43:22.462
And every day he doesn't.
people will die!

511
00:43:23.011 --> 00:43:28.631
Starting tonight.
I'm a man of my word.

512
00:43:45.344 --> 00:43:51.782
Harvey Dent. scourge of the underworld.
scared stiff by the trust fund brigade.

513
00:43:51.785 --> 00:43:53.187
- I'll be back.
- Rachel!

514
00:43:53.188 --> 00:43:55.285
A little liquid courage.
Mr Dent?

515
00:43:56.968 --> 00:43:58.872
- Alfred. right?
- That's right. sir.

516
00:43:58.873 --> 00:44:02.025
Rachel talks about you all the time.
You've known her for her whole life?

517
00:44:02.026 --> 00:44:03.143
Not yet. sir.

518
00:44:05.829 --> 00:44:08.190
Any psychotic ex-boyfriends
I should be aware of?

519
00:44:08.191 --> 00:44:10.011
Oh. you have no idea!

520
00:44:28.957 --> 00:44:33.124
I'm sorry that I'm late. but I'm glad
to see that you all got started without me.

521
00:44:33.325 --> 00:44:39.606
Now. where is Harvey?
Where is Harvey Dent. the man of the hour!

522
00:44:39.607 --> 00:44:43.774
And where's Rachel Dawes.
she is my oldest friend. Come here.

523
00:44:43.775 --> 00:44:47.897
When Rachel first told me that she was
dating Harvey Dent. I had one thing to say:

524
00:44:47.898 --> 00:44:52.376
"The guy that was cut off from those awful campaign
commercials. I believe in Harvey Dent? "

525
00:44:52.377 --> 00:44:56.682
Yeah nice slogan. Harvey.
But you caught Rachel's attention.

526
00:44:56.683 --> 00:45:03.500
Then I started to pay attention to Harvey
and all that he's been doing as our new DA.

527
00:45:03.501 --> 00:45:08.845
And you know what?
I believe in Harvey Dent.

528
00:45:08.846 --> 00:45:13.514
I believe that on his watch
Gotham can feel a little safer.

529
00:45:14.511 --> 00:45:16.978
A little more optimistic.

530
00:45:17.843 --> 00:45:22.260
Look at this face.
This is the face of Gotham's bright future.

531
00:45:22.261 --> 00:45:24.950
To Harvey Dent.
Let's hear it for him.

532
00:45:35.895 --> 00:45:39.380
Harvey may not know you well enough
to understand when you are making fun of him.

533
00:45:39.381 --> 00:45:40.383
but I do.

534
00:45:40.024 --> 00:45:41.597
No. I meant every word.

535
00:45:42.785 --> 00:45:48.051
You know that day that you once told me about
when Gotham would no longer need Batman?

536
00:45:48.125 --> 00:45:49.494
- It's coming.
- Bruce ...

537
00:45:50.637 --> 00:45:54.283
- You can't ask me to wait for that.
- It's happening now.

538
00:45:54.284 --> 00:45:56.084
Harvey is that hero.

539
00:45:56.085 --> 00:46:00.671
He locked up half of the city's criminals
and he did it without wearing a mask.

540
00:46:01.038 --> 00:46:03.781
Gotham needs a hero with a face.

541
00:46:04.458 --> 00:46:09.165
You throw a party Wayne. I'll give you that.
Thanks again.

542
00:46:10.502 --> 00:46:12.237
You mind if I borrow Rachel?

543
00:46:16.777 --> 00:46:19.367
Lieutenant. that Joker card
pinned to the body?

544
00:46:19.368 --> 00:46:21.363
Forensics found 3 sets of DNA.

545
00:46:21.398 --> 00:46:22.812
- Any matches?
- All three.

546
00:46:22.813 --> 00:46:26.229
The DNA belongs to Judge Surrillo.
Harvey Dent. and Commissioner Loeb.

547
00:46:26.230 --> 00:46:28.631
The Joker is telling us
who he's targeting.

548
00:46:28.632 --> 00:46:31.505
Get a unit over to Surrillo's house.
Tell Wuertz to find Dent.

549
00:46:31.506 --> 00:46:33.856
Get them both into protective custody.
Where's the commissioner?

550
00:46:33.857 --> 00:46:34.511
City Hall.

551
00:46:34.712 --> 00:46:37.129
Seal the building.
No one in or out until I get there.

552
00:46:37.130 --> 00:46:37.730
Got it.

553
00:46:49.989 --> 00:46:53.207
- Gordon! What are you up to?
- We're secure.

554
00:46:53.208 --> 00:46:55.707
I want a floor by floor
search of the entire building.

555
00:46:55.708 --> 00:46:58.267
Sorry sir. we believe the Joker
has made a threat against your life.

556
00:46:58.502 --> 00:46:59.974
These are dangerous people. Judge.

557
00:46:59.975 --> 00:47:02.096
Yes. but you're not
giving me an awful lot of information.

558
00:47:02.131 --> 00:47:04.792
- Even we don't know where you're going.
- Take the envelope.

559
00:47:04.793 --> 00:47:07.208
Get in. open it. It'll tell
you where you're headed.

560
00:47:11.274 --> 00:47:13.113
You can not leave me alone
with these people.

561
00:47:13.172 --> 00:47:16.343
The whole mob is after you
and you're worried about these guys?

562
00:47:16.344 --> 00:47:18.433
Compared to this.
the mob doesn't scare me.

563
00:47:18.634 --> 00:47:21.881
Gordon. you're unlikely
to discover this for yourself. so..

564
00:47:22.432 --> 00:47:26.672
Take my word. the Police Commissioner
there's a lot of threats.

565
00:47:26.673 --> 00:47:31.676
I found the appropriate response
to these situations a long time ago.

566
00:47:32.410 --> 00:47:34.623
Them gunning for you
makes you see things clearly.

567
00:47:34.624 --> 00:47:35.699
Yeah. I bet.

568
00:47:35.700 --> 00:47:39.972
Yeah. it makes you think
about things you couldn't stand losing.

569
00:47:40.959 --> 00:47:42.834
About who you want to
spend the rest of your life with.

570
00:47:42.835 --> 00:47:44.136
It's a pretty big commitment.

571
00:47:44.280 --> 00:47:45.717
Well. not if the Mob has their way.

572
00:47:50.986 --> 00:47:56.190
It'd be good to explain to my wife
why I'm late for dinner tonight.

573
00:47:56.191 --> 00:47:59.018
Sir. the Joker card
had traces of your DNA on it.

574
00:48:00.954 --> 00:48:05.675
- Don't do that.
- Alright. Let's be serious then.

575
00:48:06.233 --> 00:48:08.956
- Okay.
- What's your answer?

576
00:48:14.646 --> 00:48:16.959
I don't have an answer.

577
00:48:18.366 --> 00:48:19.750
How'd they get my DNA?

578
00:48:19.751 --> 00:48:21.588
Somebody with access to your
office or your house

579
00:48:21.589 --> 00:48:23.811
must have lifted a tissue
or a glass...

580
00:48:23.846 --> 00:48:24.641
Wait!

581
00:48:24.975 --> 00:48:27.186
- I guess the answer is no.
- Harvey ...

582
00:48:27.667 --> 00:48:29.661
- It's someone else. isn't it?
- Harvey!

583
00:48:29.939 --> 00:48:32.540
Just tell me it's not Wayne.
the guy's a complete…

584
00:48:33.650 --> 00:48:35.385
What are you doing?

585
00:48:53.583 --> 00:48:55.320
Get a medic!

586
00:49:01.320 --> 00:49:02.428
We made it!

587
00:49:08.343 --> 00:49:11.643
Good evening. ladies and gentlemen.

588
00:49:14.437 --> 00:49:17.610
We are tonight's entertainment!

589
00:49:19.309 --> 00:49:20.784
I only have one question.

590
00:49:21.752 --> 00:49:24.517
Where is Harvey Dent?

591
00:49:34.753 --> 00:49:37.085
You know where Harvey is?
You know who he is?

592
00:49:37.057 --> 00:49:38.703
Hands up. pretty boy!

593
00:49:45.246 --> 00:49:46.919
Do you know where I can find Harvey?

594
00:49:46.920 --> 00:49:49.621
I need to talk to him about something.
something little.

595
00:49:50.330 --> 00:49:51.223
No. ..

596
00:49:53.157 --> 00:49:55.655
- What's going on out there?
- Wayne!

597
00:49:57.902 --> 00:50:00.100
Ah. thank God  you've
got a panic room. Wait!

598
00:50:00.915 --> 00:50:02.643
You got to be kidding me.

599
00:50:02.972 --> 00:50:08.166
- You know. I'll settle for his loved ones.
- We're not intimidated by thugs!

600
00:50:09.577 --> 00:50:15.132
You know. you remind me of my father.

601
00:50:16.426 --> 00:50:20.004
- I hated my father!
- Okay stop!

602
00:50:24.339 --> 00:50:31.770
Well. hello beautiful!
You must be Harvey's squeeze!

603
00:50:33.523 --> 00:50:35.448
And you are beautiful.

604
00:50:42.707 --> 00:50:45.978
You look nervous.
Is it the scars?

605
00:50:47.728 --> 00:50:49.392
You want to know how I got them?

606
00:50:50.803 --> 00:50:53.016
Come here.
Hey!

607
00:50:53.872 --> 00:50:55.384
Look at me.

608
00:50:56.137 --> 00:51:00.120
So I had a wife. beautiful. like you.

609
00:51:01.062 --> 00:51:07.949
who tells me I worry too much.
Who tells me I ought to smile more.

610
00:51:08.504 --> 00:51:13.366
Who gambles and gets in deep with the sharks

611
00:51:14.330 --> 00:51:19.184
One day. they carve her face.
And we have no money for surgeries.

612
00:51:19.185 --> 00:51:24.128
She can't take it.
I just want to see her smile again. hmm?

613
00:51:25.623 --> 00:51:28.633
I just want her to know
that I don't care about the scars.

614
00:51:28.949 --> 00:51:36.721
So... I stick a razor in my mouth
and do this... to myself

615
00:51:37.113 --> 00:51:44.096
And you know what?
She can't stand the sight of me! She leaves.

616
00:51:44.531 --> 00:51:49.948
Now I see the funny side.
Now I'm always smiling!

617
00:51:53.018 --> 00:51:56.491
A little fight in you.
I like that.

618
00:51:56.492 --> 00:51:57.766
Then you're going to love me.

619
00:52:26.790 --> 00:52:29.344
- Drop the gun.
- Oh. sure!

620
00:52:29.345 --> 00:52:32.701
You just take off your little
mask and show us all who you really are.

621
00:52:38.786 --> 00:52:42.803
- Let her go.
- Very poor choice of words!

622
00:53:04.562 --> 00:53:06.157
Are you alright?

623
00:53:09.036 --> 00:53:10.581
Let's not do that again ...

624
00:53:11.717 --> 00:53:13.797
- Is Harvey okay?
- He's safe.

625
00:53:15.442 --> 00:53:16.505
Thank you

626
00:53:17.228 --> 00:53:18.348
Jim. it's over!

627
00:53:18.483 --> 00:53:21.272
As long as they don't get to Lau.
we've cut off their funds.

628
00:53:21.346 --> 00:53:22.827
But the prosecution is over!

629
00:53:22.828 --> 00:53:27.378
Nobody's standing up in front of a judge while judges
and police commissioners are getting blown away.

630
00:53:27.842 --> 00:53:28.879
What about Dent?

631
00:53:29.081 --> 00:53:30.746
If he's got any sense.
Dent's halfway to Mexico.

632
00:53:31.332 --> 00:53:32.805
So where do you keep your trash?

633
00:53:34.085 --> 00:53:35.186
You're due at court.

634
00:53:36.121 --> 00:53:37.677
I need you alive long enough
to get you under record.

635
00:53:38.190 --> 00:53:41.055
You can't protect me.
You can't even protect yourselves.

636
00:53:41.091 --> 00:53:44.059
If you refuse to cooperate you're
not coming back here. you go to county.

637
00:53:44.455 --> 00:53:46.717
How long you calculate
you'll last in there?

638
00:53:48.485 --> 00:53:50.549
Targeting me won't get
their money back.

639
00:53:50.550 --> 00:53:53.453
I knew the mob wouldn't go down
without a fight. but this is different.

640
00:53:53.474 --> 00:53:55.795
- They've crossed the line.
- You've crossed the line first.sir

641
00:53:55.796 --> 00:53:59.154
You squeezed them. you hammered
them to the point of desperation.

642
00:53:59.813 --> 00:54:03.956
In their desperation. they turned to
a man they didn't fully understand.

643
00:54:05.714 --> 00:54:07.510
Criminals aren't complicated Alfred.

644
00:54:08.141 --> 00:54:10.244
We just need to figure out what he's after.

645
00:54:10.245 --> 00:54:15.046
With respect. master Wayne. perhaps this
is a man you don't fully understand either.

646
00:54:15.593 --> 00:54:18.903
A long time ago I was in Burma.

647
00:54:18.904 --> 00:54:22.198
My friends and I were working
for the local government.

648
00:54:22.323 --> 00:54:24.863
They were trying to buy the
loyalty of tribal leaders by

649
00:54:24.864 --> 00:54:27.421
bribing them with precious stones.

650
00:54:27.912 --> 00:54:32.559
But their caravans were being raided
in a forest north of Yangoon by a bandit.

651
00:54:32.560 --> 00:54:34.965
So. we went looking for the stones.

652
00:54:36.284 --> 00:54:41.696
But in 6 months we never met
anyone who traded with him.

653
00:54:42.083 --> 00:54:48.663
One day. I saw a child playing with
a ruby the size of a tangerine.

654
00:54:49.570 --> 00:54:54.611
- The bandit had been throwing them away.
- So why steal them?

655
00:54:54.612 --> 00:54:56.658
Well. because he thought
it was good sport.

656
00:54:56.659 --> 00:55:01.031
Because some men aren't looking
for anything logical. like money.

657
00:55:01.421 --> 00:55:06.189
They can't be bought. bullied.
reasoned. or negotiated with.

658
00:55:06.190 --> 00:55:09.976
Some men just want
to watch the world burn.

659
00:55:47.959 --> 00:55:49.510
Get the names.

660
00:55:55.851 --> 00:56:01.209
- Richard Dent
- Patrick Harvey

661
00:56:01.522 --> 00:56:02.490
Harvey Dent.

662
00:56:02.658 --> 00:56:05.532
I need 10 minutes with the scene
before your men contaminate it.

663
00:56:05.668 --> 00:56:08.003
Us contaminate it? It's because
of you these guys are dead ...

664
00:56:08.004 --> 00:56:09.005
Detective!

665
00:56:11.448 --> 00:56:13.583
Just a minute guys.

666
00:56:15.160 --> 00:56:16.907
It's brick underneath.

667
00:56:17.260 --> 00:56:19.024
You going to take ballistics
off a shattered bullet?

668
00:56:19.025 --> 00:56:23.783
No.
Fingerprints.

669
00:56:30.408 --> 00:56:32.108
Obituaries.
Mayor Anthony Garcia.

670
00:56:32.109 --> 00:56:34.296
Whatever you're going to do.
do it fast.

671
00:56:36.226 --> 00:56:40.856
Because we found his next target.
He's put it in tomorrow's paper.

672
00:56:58.135 --> 00:57:00.247
I'm not sure you
made it loud enough. sir.

673
00:57:13.442 --> 00:57:14.824
What can I do for you Mr Reese?

674
00:57:15.554 --> 00:57:18.357
You wanted me to do the
diligence on the LSI holdings deal again.

675
00:57:20.192 --> 00:57:24.973
- Well. I found some irregularities.
- Our CEO is in police custody.

676
00:57:24.974 --> 00:57:27.867
No. not with their numbers
With yours.

677
00:57:28.264 --> 00:57:29.307
Applied sciences.

678
00:57:29.308 --> 00:57:33.395
A whole division of Wayne
Enterprises just disappeared. overnight.

679
00:57:33.396 --> 00:57:36.986
I went down to the archives and
I started pulling some old files.

680
00:57:38.484 --> 00:57:40.414
Don't tell me you didn't
recognize your baby out there

681
00:57:40.415 --> 00:57:43.135
pancaking cop cars on the evening news.

682
00:57:44.521 --> 00:57:48.587
Now you got the entire RND
department burning through cash

683
00:57:48.588 --> 00:57:51.328
claiming it's related
to cellphones for the army?

684
00:57:51.329 --> 00:57:54.982
What are you building for
him now. a rocket ship?

685
00:57:56.833 --> 00:58:02.355
I want 10 million dollars
a year for the rest of my life.

686
00:58:04.958 --> 00:58:06.978
Let me get this straight.

687
00:58:08.653 --> 00:58:14.495
You think that your client. one of the
wealthiest. most powerful men in the world

688
00:58:14.496 --> 00:58:19.031
is secretly a vigilante. who spends his
nights beating criminals to a pulp ...

689
00:58:19.032 --> 00:58:24.420
... with his bare hands.
And your plan is to blackmail this person?

690
00:58:31.466 --> 00:58:32.867
Good luck.

691
00:58:38.534 --> 00:58:39.650
Keep that.

692
00:58:46.806 --> 00:58:48.711
This is your original scan.

693
00:58:50.577 --> 00:58:52.440
Here it is re-engineered.

694
00:59:01.164 --> 00:59:03.927
And there's the thumbprint he left when
he pushed the round in the clip.

695
00:59:06.369 --> 00:59:07.862
I'll get you a copy.

696
00:59:08.041 --> 00:59:12.409
Mr. Wayne. did you reassign RND?

697
00:59:12.410 --> 00:59:14.447
Yes. government
telecommunications project.

698
00:59:14.448 --> 00:59:16.571
I wasn't aware we had any
government contracts.

699
00:59:16.839 --> 00:59:19.932
Lucius. I'm playing
this one pretty close to the chest.

700
00:59:20.933 --> 00:59:22.448
Fair enough.

701
00:59:25.952 --> 00:59:29.137
With no word from the Batman.
Even as they mourn Commissioner Loeb.

702
00:59:29.138 --> 00:59:32.211
These cops have to be wondering
if the Joker will make good on

703
00:59:32.212 --> 00:59:35.415
his threat in the obituary column of
the Gotham Times to kill the mayor.

704
00:59:37.796 --> 00:59:41.680
I've checked all the databases.
There are four possibles.

705
00:59:41.681 --> 00:59:47.749
Cross reference the addresses. Look
for Park Side. overlooking the parade.

706
00:59:49.400 --> 00:59:54.665
I got one! Melvin White.
1502 Randalf Apartments

707
00:59:54.861 --> 00:59:58.535
Aggravated his soul.
moved to Arkham twice.

708
01:00:37.732 --> 01:00:39.043
How many you got on the roof?

709
01:00:39.521 --> 01:00:42.397
We're tight but frankly
there's a lot of windows up here!

710
01:00:51.486 --> 01:00:54.968
Commissioner Loeb
dedicated his life to

711
01:00:54.969 --> 01:00:57.954
law enforcement and to
the protection of his community.

712
01:00:58.189 --> 01:00:59.948
I remember when I first took office.

713
01:00:59.949 --> 01:01:02.310
I asked him if
he wanted to stay on as Commissioner and...

714
01:01:11.669 --> 01:01:15.046
Clearly he was not a man who minced
words nor should he have been

715
01:01:16.440 --> 01:01:20.352
A number of policies that
he enacted were unpopular.

716
01:01:20.353 --> 01:01:23.461
Policies that flooded
my office with angry calls and letter ...

717
01:01:27.861 --> 01:01:29.530
- Who is it?
- What happened?

718
01:01:30.547 --> 01:01:34.596
They took our guns and uniforms.

719
01:01:43.664 --> 01:01:47.769
We must remember that vigilance
is the price of safety.

720
01:01:48.105 --> 01:01:51.309
Standby. Honor. Guard. Atten-hut.

721
01:01:55.190 --> 01:01:56.711
Ready

722
01:01:56.712 --> 01:01:57.802
Aim

723
01:01:58.390 --> 01:01:59.884
Fire!

724
01:02:00.891 --> 01:02:03.653
Ready. aim ...

725
01:02:05.842 --> 01:02:08.602
Ready. aim ...

726
01:02:20.038 --> 01:02:21.310
Get him out!

727
01:02:30.609 --> 01:02:32.390
- I'll see you later!
- Why are you coming back?

728
01:02:45.027 --> 01:02:46.255
Get out!

729
01:02:50.711 --> 01:02:52.952
Tell me what you
know about the Joker.

730
01:03:23.543 --> 01:03:26.867
- No!
- I'm sorry Barbara.

731
01:03:27.253 --> 01:03:30.272
Junior. go play with
your sister. go ahead.

732
01:03:31.221 --> 01:03:35.304
If there is anything that
I can do. we're here for you.

733
01:03:39.309 --> 01:03:46.414
Are you happy ..Are you
You brought this craziness on us ... You did!

734
01:03:49.304 --> 01:03:53.373
Switch it off. he ain't coming.
He doesn't want to talk to us.

735
01:03:54.483 --> 01:03:57.165
May God help whoever
he does want to talk to.

736
01:03:58.266 --> 01:04:01.113
Can we go some place quieter?
We can't hear each other talk.

737
01:04:01.563 --> 01:04:04.411
Why makes you think
I want to hear you talk?

738
01:04:04.786 --> 01:04:05.505
What?

739
01:04:38.477 --> 01:04:40.845
- Harvey. where are you?
- Where are you?

740
01:04:40.846 --> 01:04:44.384
I'm where you should be at MCU
I'm trying to deal with all this mess.

741
01:04:44.385 --> 01:04:45.586
Can I get the fingerprint analysis?

742
01:04:45.587 --> 01:04:48.419
Rachel. listen to me.
You're not safe there.

743
01:04:48.420 --> 01:04:50.675
- Oh. this is Gordon's unit.
- Gordon's gone. Rachel.

744
01:04:50.676 --> 01:04:53.385
- He vouched for these men.
- And he's gone.

745
01:04:58.567 --> 01:05:00.885
The Joker has named you next.

746
01:05:00.933 --> 01:05:03.869
Is there anyone in this
town we can trust?

747
01:05:04.121 --> 01:05:07.350
Bruce.
We can trust Bruce Wayne.

748
01:05:07.351 --> 01:05:09.357
No Rachel. I know
you're his friend but ...

749
01:05:09.358 --> 01:05:10.359
Harvey. Trust me.

750
01:05:11.177 --> 01:05:14.276
Bruce's penthouse is now
the safest place in the city.

751
01:05:14.277 --> 01:05:17.994
Then you go straight there. Don't tell
anybody where you're going. I'll find you there.

752
01:05:17.995 --> 01:05:19.196
I love you.

753
01:05:33.499 --> 01:05:34.956
I want the Joker.

754
01:05:36.130 --> 01:05:40.562
From one professional to another. if you're
trying to scare somebody. pick a better spot.

755
01:05:40.563 --> 01:05:43.167
From this height. the fall wouldn't kill me.

756
01:05:43.168 --> 01:05:44.319
I'm counting on it.

757
01:05:52.295 --> 01:05:53.211
Where is he?

758
01:05:53.212 --> 01:05:55.512
I don't know where he is.
He found us.

759
01:05:55.513 --> 01:05:59.452
- He must have friends.
- Friends? Have you met this guy?

760
01:05:59.453 --> 01:06:03.723
- Someone knows where he is!
- Nobody's going to tell you nothing.

761
01:06:03.724 --> 01:06:07.987
He was right.
You got rules. The Joker...

762
01:06:07.988 --> 01:06:11.852
He's got no rules.
Nobody's going to cross him for you.

763
01:06:11.853 --> 01:06:16.210
If you want this guy. you got one way.
But you already know what that is.

764
01:06:16.211 --> 01:06:19.746
Just take off that mask
let him come find you.

765
01:06:21.209 --> 01:06:24.891
Or are you going to let a couple more
people get killed while you make up your mind.

766
01:06:26.595 --> 01:06:28.197
You want to play games?

767
01:06:35.337 --> 01:06:36.490
How's that feel?

768
01:06:36.491 --> 01:06:38.433
- Don't kill ...
- I wouldn't?

769
01:06:40.457 --> 01:06:43.409
You don't think I will?
You don't think I will?

770
01:06:45.447 --> 01:06:48.279
No. I wouldn't.

771
01:06:49.787 --> 01:06:51.883
That's why I'm not going
to leave it up to me.

772
01:06:53.441 --> 01:07:00.668
Heads. you get to keep your head.
Tails. not so lucky.

773
01:07:00.669 --> 01:07:03.458
So. you want to tell me about the Joker?

774
01:07:13.709 --> 01:07:17.435
- Let's go again.
- I don't know anything. I don't!

775
01:07:17.752 --> 01:07:22.283
You're not playing the odds. friend.
Let's do it again.

776
01:07:25.650 --> 01:07:29.685
- You'd leave a man's life to chance?
- Not exactly.

777
01:07:29.686 --> 01:07:31.955
His name is Shif. Thomas.

778
01:07:31.956 --> 01:07:35.932
He's a paranoid schizophrenic.
former patient at Arkham.

779
01:07:35.933 --> 01:07:37.634
The kind of mind
that Joker attracts.

780
01:07:38.134 --> 01:07:40.070
What do you expect to learn from him?

781
01:07:43.990 --> 01:07:46.878
The Joker killed Gordon.
He's going to kill Rachel!

782
01:07:46.879 --> 01:07:49.574
You are the symbol of hope
I could never be.

783
01:07:49.776 --> 01:07:52.453
Your stand against organized
crime is the first

784
01:07:52.454 --> 01:07:55.201
legitimate ray of light in
Gotham in decades.

785
01:07:55.236 --> 01:07:58.249
If anyone saw this.
everything would be undone.

786
01:07:59.124 --> 01:08:01.226
All the criminals you pulled off
the streets would be released

787
01:08:01.227 --> 01:08:03.688
and Jim Gordon will have died for nothing.

788
01:08:05.279 --> 01:08:08.321
- You're going to hold a press
conference tomorrow morning.
- Why?

789
01:08:08.322 --> 01:08:11.744
No one else will die because of me.
Gotham is in your hands now.

790
01:08:12.552 --> 01:08:16.013
You can't.
You can't give in.

791
01:08:16.014 --> 01:08:17.015
You can't give in!

792
01:08:34.036 --> 01:08:38.223
Harvey called.
He said Batman's going to turn himself in.

793
01:08:38.707 --> 01:08:39.673
I have no choice.

794
01:08:39.674 --> 01:08:43.266
Do you honestly think that's going to
keep the Joker from killing people?

795
01:08:43.267 --> 01:08:45.977
Maybe not. but I have
enough blood on my hands.

796
01:08:47.085 --> 01:08:51.676
I have seen now what I would have to
become to stop a man like him.

797
01:08:52.590 --> 01:08:55.226
You once told me that if
the day came when I...

798
01:08:55.227 --> 01:08:57.108
was finished. then we would be together.

799
01:08:58.802 --> 01:09:01.855
Bruce. don't make me your
one hope for a normal life.

800
01:09:03.481 --> 01:09:04.744
Did you mean it?

801
01:09:06.290 --> 01:09:07.574
Yes.

802
01:09:27.738 --> 01:09:31.692
If you turn yourself in. they're
not going to let us be together.

803
01:09:43.153 --> 01:09:46.051
- Logs as well?
- Everything.

804
01:09:46.052 --> 01:09:49.219
Anything that can
lead back to Lucius or Rachel.

805
01:09:55.174 --> 01:09:58.267
People are dying Alfred.
What would you have me do?

806
01:09:58.368 --> 01:10:03.661
- Endure ... master Wayne.
- Take it .... They'll hate you for it.

807
01:10:04.070 --> 01:10:07.967
But that's the point of Batman.
he can be the outcast.

808
01:10:07.968 --> 01:10:13.181
He can make the choice that
no one else can make.  the right choice.

809
01:10:13.581 --> 01:10:18.084
Well today I found out what Batman can't do.
He can't endure this.

810
01:10:18.085 --> 01:10:20.687
Today you get to say
"I told you so."

811
01:10:21.789 --> 01:10:24.577
Today. I don't want to.

812
01:10:30.900 --> 01:10:32.689
But I did bloody tell you.

813
01:10:35.402 --> 01:10:40.533
I suppose they'll lock me up as well.
As your accomplice...

814
01:10:40.534 --> 01:10:44.259
Accomplice? I'm going to tell them
the whole thing was your idea.

815
01:10:49.565 --> 01:10:51.017
Ladies and Gentlemen.
Thank you for coming.

816
01:10:51.018 --> 01:10:53.276
I've called this
press conference for two reasons.

817
01:10:53.277 --> 01:10:55.739
Firstly. to assure
the citizens of Gotham that

818
01:10:55.740 --> 01:10:59.248
everything that can be done over
the Joker killings is being done.

819
01:11:00.126 --> 01:11:02.930
Secondly. because the Batman
has offered to turn himself in.

820
01:11:03.629 --> 01:11:05.283
But first. let's consider the situation.

821
01:11:05.284 --> 01:11:07.537
Should we give into
this terrorist's demands?

822
01:11:08.550 --> 01:11:11.536
- Do we really think that ...
- Would you rather protect an outlaw vigilante

823
01:11:11.537 --> 01:11:13.587
... than the lives of citizens?

824
01:11:13.588 --> 01:11:15.094
The Batman is an outlaw.

825
01:11:16.993 --> 01:11:18.921
But that's not why
we're demanding he turn himself in.

826
01:11:18.956 --> 01:11:20.405
We're doing it because we're scared.

827
01:11:20.606 --> 01:11:23.407
We've been happy to let the Batman
clean up our streets for us until now.

828
01:11:23.408 --> 01:11:25.518
Things are worse than ever!

829
01:11:27.992 --> 01:11:29.296
Yes they are ...

830
01:11:32.306 --> 01:11:34.906
But the night is darkest
just before the dawn.

831
01:11:38.062 --> 01:11:42.116
And I promise you ...
the dawn is coming.

832
01:11:42.217 --> 01:11:45.420
One day. the Batman will have to
answer for the laws he's broken.

833
01:11:45.421 --> 01:11:48.372
But to us. not to this madman!

834
01:11:48.995 --> 01:11:50.538
No more dead cops!

835
01:11:54.455 --> 01:11:56.580
He should turn himself in!

836
01:12:02.353 --> 01:12:04.587
So be it.
Take the Batman into custody.

837
01:12:07.887 --> 01:12:09.098
I am the Batman.

838
01:12:19.968 --> 01:12:21.267
Alfred!

839
01:12:23.041 --> 01:12:25.274
Why is he letting Harvey do this?

840
01:12:25.346 --> 01:12:28.112
- He went down to the press conference.
- I know. and he just stoodby!

841
01:12:28.151 --> 01:12:31.453
Perhaps both Bruce and
Mr. Dent believe the Batman

842
01:12:31.491 --> 01:12:35.295
stands for something more important than
the whims of a terrorist. Ms. Dawes.

843
01:12:36.033 --> 01:12:38.059
Even if everyone hates him for it.

844
01:12:38.471 --> 01:12:40.463
That's a sacrifice he's making.

845
01:12:40.876 --> 01:12:44.611
He's not being a hero.
He is being something more.

846
01:12:44.683 --> 01:12:49.488
Yeah. you're absolutely right. Letting Harvey
take the fall for this is not heroic at all.

847
01:12:52.298 --> 01:12:55.737
- You know him better than anyone.
- I do.

848
01:12:58.442 --> 01:13:02.440
Will you give this to him for me?
When the time is right.

849
01:13:02.952 --> 01:13:06.254
- How will I know?
- It's not sealed.

850
01:13:07.761 --> 01:13:09.196
- Bye Alfred.

851
01:13:12.771 --> 01:13:14.365
- Goodbye Rachel.

852
01:13:22.991 --> 01:13:25.257
Sorry. I didn't have time
to talk this through with you ...

853
01:13:25.295 --> 01:13:26.321
What are you doing?

854
01:13:26.398 --> 01:13:27.991
They're transferring me
to Central holding.

855
01:13:29.203 --> 01:13:31.730
This is the Joker's chance. And when
he attacks. the Batman will take him down.

856
01:13:31.808 --> 01:13:34.075
Listen to me. this is too dangerous!

857
01:13:34.113 --> 01:13:36.208
We get this guy to county.
he's their problem.

858
01:13:36.251 --> 01:13:38.244
The streets will be cleared
along your route. Let's go!

859
01:13:38.355 --> 01:13:41.326
Lieutenant. the convoy stops for no reason!

860
01:13:42.029 --> 01:13:43.363
I hope you got some moves pal.

861
01:13:43.364 --> 01:13:46.515
He's using you as bait. He doesn't
even know if he can get the Joker.

862
01:13:46.516 --> 01:13:49.118
- He's failed so far.
- How do you know what he's looking for?

863
01:13:49.119 --> 01:13:50.119
I just. I do!

864
01:13:50.420 --> 01:13:52.174
Anyway Harvey.
this isn't just about you.

865
01:13:52.175 --> 01:13:56.291
What about all the people who are depending on
you to clean the city up and to do it honorably?

866
01:14:02.707 --> 01:14:05.771
Harvey. tell everyone the truth.

867
01:14:05.772 --> 01:14:07.137
Heads. I go through with it.

868
01:14:07.814 --> 01:14:11.749
This is your life! You can't leave
something like that to chance.

869
01:14:12.297 --> 01:14:13.253
I'm not.

870
01:14:16.359 --> 01:14:18.500
You make your own luck.

871
01:14:41.365 --> 01:14:43.076
Hey! You wait like
everyone else. pal.

872
01:14:50.965 --> 01:14:55.123
What the hell is that?
Obstruction ahead! Obstruction ahead!

873
01:14:55.819 --> 01:14:59.571
Damn it! All units. divert down onto
lower 5th. I repeat. exit down.

874
01:14:59.572 --> 01:15:03.321
- Exit down!
- Lower 5th? We'll be like
turkeys on Thanksgiving down there.

875
01:15:36.647 --> 01:15:38.187
Come on. Get us out of here.
Let's go

876
01:15:40.308 --> 01:15:42.596
Listen. we need backup.
We've got company.

877
01:15:42.597 --> 01:15:43.771
We got trouble. guys.

878
01:15:47.037 --> 01:15:47.998
Lock and load!

879
01:15:59.296 --> 01:16:00.580
What the hell was that?

880
01:16:22.762 --> 01:16:24.266
These things were
built for that. right?

881
01:16:24.267 --> 01:16:26.325
He's going to need something
a lot bigger to get through this.

882
01:16:28.487 --> 01:16:29.122
What is that?

883
01:16:30.994 --> 01:16:32.275
What is that? A bazooka!

884
01:16:40.949 --> 01:16:42.242
I didn't sign up for this!

885
01:16:59.041 --> 01:16:59.786
Look out.

886
01:17:01.144 --> 01:17:01.699
Down!

887
01:17:24.857 --> 01:17:26.025
Come on! Let's go!

888
01:18:12.460 --> 01:18:17.832
Harvey. Harvey. Harvey Dent!
Excuse me. I want to drive.

889
01:18:22.436 --> 01:18:25.815
Scanning all systems.
Scanning all systems.

890
01:18:33.460 --> 01:18:35.876
We got to get topside.
We need air support now.

891
01:18:41.253 --> 01:18:43.240
I like this job! I like it!

892
01:18:45.289 --> 01:18:48.427
Damage catastrophic.
Eject sequence initiated.

893
01:19:01.987 --> 01:19:02.717
Goodbye.

894
01:19:12.745 --> 01:19:14.972
We're on point! Ready to give them
some of their own medicine.

895
01:19:22.185 --> 01:19:24.458
That's what I'm talking about.
Aircabs.

896
01:19:38.314 --> 01:19:41.546
Okay! Rack 'em up. rack 'em up.
rack 'em up!

897
01:20:08.264 --> 01:20:09.174
That's not good.

898
01:20:13.007 --> 01:20:14.194
Okay. That's not good!
